org.midao.jdbc.core.handlers.output.lazy
Interface LazyUpdateOutputHandler<T,S>

All Known Subinterfaces:

All Known Implementing Classes:

public interface LazyUpdateOutputHandler<T,S>
extends LazyOutputHandler<T,S>

If underlying JDBC Driver doesn't support updateable ResultSet - exception would be thrown. In order to check if JDBC Driver supports such functionality - please read relevant JDBC driver documentation and/or create POC (Proof of concept).

Update supports only one ResultSet due to the fact that some JDBC Drivers close previous ResultSet before returning next one. In cases where multiple ResultSets need to be handled - please use cached or standard(non-scrollable) lazy output.
